  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "English Teacher",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Teach English to young learners and primary-level students using engaging and age-appropriate methods.</li><li>Plan and deliver lessons that develop reading, writing, speaking, and listening skills.</li><li>Monitor student progress and provide constructive feedback to students and parents.</li><li>Create a positive, supportive, and well-managed classroom environment.</li><li>Collaborate with the academic team to ensure lesson quality and consistency.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>A recognized degree in a relevant discipline such as Teaching, Education, Early Childhood Studies, English, English Literature, or Linguistics is preferred.</li><li>Candidates with a diploma qualification must have formal training in a closely related field, including Teaching, Education, Early Childhood Studies, English Language, English Literature, or Linguistics.</li><li>A minimum of two years of relevant teaching experience or equivalent professional experience in a related role.</li><li>Proven experience teaching young learners and/or primary students.</li><li>Strong classroom management and communication skills.</li><li>Passion for working with children and supporting their learning journey.</li></ul><p><strong>Nice to Have (Plus):</strong></p><ul><li>Curriculum writing or lesson material development experience.</li><li>Familiarity with local primary English curricula.</li></ul>",
